g.text: PWM signal generator for brightness control
Using a 1MEG rotary thumbwheel potentiometer (VR) to control pulse width.
Draw from USB connector at worst case: 425mA @ 5V (2.125W)
Draw from USB connector during MCU modem-sleep: 270mA @ 5V (1.35W)
Using MOSFETS cause the shift register cannot
source/sink the currents needed by the LED array.
Mini display board for testing and evaluating a USB Type-C interface for Micro-controllers.
